My two cents is that codecademy is good for learning syntax whereas the long written project style is good for learning frameworks. They can both be good for teaching concepts.
Maybe another question is why Make School consciously chose our current styles of tutorials? <@UEPUV52GL> :slightly_smiling_face:

Adding onto what <@UCC0GD5V0> said the interactive tutorial component of Codeacademy helps me walk through code rather than reading a block of text, then typing out or copy pasting into my code editor and seeing if it works. I really like the controlled learning environment they put you in I guess, not sure exactly what it is tbh.

I think the core difference is the way they are chunked and the instant feedback. With codecademy style tutorials you know immediately if you got something right or not. It's light gamification that makes it easier to go through a whole bunch in one sitting.
